WEBVTT

1
00:01:38.269 --> 00:01:42.189
Yes, ladies and gentlemen,
we are in luck today here in Los Angeles.


2
00:01:42.482 --> 00:01:44.775
Through the years,
the Bullwinkle Galleries...


3
00:01:44.984 --> 00:01:46.568
...have brought up for auction...

4
00:01:46.778 --> 00:01:50.948
...many collections of the personal effects
of your famous movie stars.


5
00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:55.369
But today is indeed a red-letter day.

6
00:01:55.578 --> 00:01:58.413
The personal effects of Tony Hunter!

7
00:01:58.790 --> 00:01:59.915
Lot 94.

8
00:02:00.124 --> 00:02:04.002
Ladies and gentlemen,
let's start out with Lot 94.


9
00:02:04.629 --> 00:02:09.091
Some of the potpourri
of Mr. Hunter's own personal costumes...


10
00:02:09.467 --> 00:02:13.053
...that he used in his famous
dancing-singing pictures.


11
00:02:13.263 --> 00:02:16.306
Remember this?
Perhaps the most famous top hat...


12
00:02:16.516 --> 00:02:18.308
...and stick of our generation.

13
00:02:18.518 --> 00:02:22.312
Yes, the one he used
in Swinging Down to Panama...


14
00:02:22.522 --> 00:02:24.606
...and all his other famous pictures.

15
00:02:24.983 --> 00:02:28.610
Let's start with $5. Do I hear $5?

16
00:02:29.153 --> 00:02:31.071
It's worth a lot more.

17
00:02:31.489 --> 00:02:33.824
All right. Let's start with 2.

18
00:02:34.367 --> 00:02:37.411
Well? Fifty cents?

19
00:02:39.455 --> 00:02:40.747
Anything?

20
00:02:49.340 --> 00:02:52.592
Just one more for the road.
About 20 minutes to New York.


21
00:02:52.802 --> 00:02:54.094
Bottoms up.

22
00:02:57.432 --> 00:03:00.142
- So you're from California?
- That's right. Sunny Cal.


23
00:03:00.351 --> 00:03:02.728
- Sunny Cal?
- Yeah. Sunny Cal.


24
00:03:03.021 --> 00:03:06.648
Say, you're from Sunny Cal. I bet
you know a lot of movie stars out there.


25
00:03:06.858 --> 00:03:08.984
I got to confess. 
I'm just like you and me.

26
00:03:09.193 --> 00:03:11.486
- Only get to see them in the movies.
- Ha, ha.


27
00:03:11.696 --> 00:03:14.281
But I read about them.
I know all about them.


28
00:03:15.450 --> 00:03:18.410
Boy, I'd sure like to meet
that Ava Gardner.


29
00:03:18.786 --> 00:03:21.413
- You're a little late. She's married.
- Yeah.


30
00:03:21.914 --> 00:03:23.749
- You know this one?
- Who's that?


31
00:03:23.958 --> 00:03:27.127
- Tony Hunter.
- Oh, him. The singing-dancing fella.


32
00:03:27.378 --> 00:03:31.381
My wife used to go see all his pictures.
Almost broke up our home.


33
00:03:31.591 --> 00:03:33.633
"Tony Hunter! Tony Hunter!"

34
00:03:34.135 --> 00:03:35.969
He was good 12 or 15 years ago...

35
00:03:36.179 --> 00:03:38.430
...but the columnists out there
say he's through.


36
00:03:39.265 --> 00:03:42.809
Through? He's washed up.
Hasn't made a picture in three years.


37
00:03:43.019 --> 00:03:45.979
- Did you say something, mister?
- I said I agreed with you.


38
00:03:46.189 --> 00:03:47.647
That Tony Hunter's a has-been.

39
00:03:47.857 --> 00:03:49.483
- Got a match?
- Yeah.


40
00:03:49.692 --> 00:03:52.861
I wouldn't go to see him
if they gave away $5 bills with the ticket.


41
00:03:54.489 --> 00:03:55.614
Yeah.

42
00:03:57.784 --> 00:03:59.701
We should be pulling...

43
00:04:00.036 --> 00:04:04.706
The funny thing about what you're saying,
boys, is that it's absolutely true.


44
00:04:04.999 --> 00:04:07.417
Here. Have an exploding cigar.

45
00:04:23.309 --> 00:04:25.560
- This the last of the bags, Mr. Hunter?
- Yeah.


46
00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:28.563
Say, porter, um, could you see that
they get put in a taxi...


47
00:04:28.773 --> 00:04:32.818
...and taken up to the, uh, Plaza Hotel?
- Yes, sir. Thank you, sir.


48
00:04:33.820 --> 00:04:35.362
Everybody's getting off, sir.

49
00:04:35.571 --> 00:04:38.824
If you don't mind,
I'll just sit for a minute or two.


50
00:04:39.033 --> 00:04:42.119
You couldn't just, uh, make up my berth
for the night here, could you?


51
00:04:42.328 --> 00:04:44.413
No, sir. I couldn't do that.

52
00:04:56.092 --> 00:04:58.802
There's a mob of reporters
and photographers out there.


53
00:04:59.011 --> 00:05:02.097
Yep. There must be some big shot aboard.
Maybe the president.


54
00:05:02.306 --> 00:05:05.392
No, too many for that.
Probably a movie star.


55
00:05:11.858 --> 00:05:14.443
- Hi, fellas.
- Tony Hunter! Hello, Mr. Hunter!


56
00:05:14.777 --> 00:05:17.279
Thanks for the red-carpet bit.
I didn't expect it.


57
00:05:17.488 --> 00:05:20.699
- What brings you to New York?
- Just fooling around.


58
00:05:20.908 --> 00:05:23.034
- Between pictures, Tony?
- In a manner of speaking.


59
00:05:23.244 --> 00:05:26.121
Didn't I read something in Variety
about you going into a show?


60
00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:29.749
Lily and Les Marton had something
planned for me. I haven't decided yet.


61
00:05:29.959 --> 00:05:33.879
I haven't been on the stage in a long time.
And you get into a different medium.


62
00:05:34.088 --> 00:05:35.839
- What it actually is...
- Here she is!


63
00:05:36.048 --> 00:05:37.924
- Excuse me, Mr. Hunter.
- See you later.


64
00:05:38.134 --> 00:05:39.217
Hi, Miss Gardner.

65
00:05:39.427 --> 00:05:41.803
Miss Gardner, hold it, please?
Smile pretty. Thanks.


66
00:05:42.013 --> 00:05:45.474
- How long you going to be in town?
- I have no definite plans.


67
00:05:45.683 --> 00:05:48.059
Tony! I had no idea
you were on the train.

68
00:05:48.269 --> 00:05:50.187
This is a surprise.
You going to be here long?


69
00:05:50.396 --> 00:05:52.606
- Perhaps a week or two...
- Excuse me, Miss Gardner.


70
00:05:52.815 --> 00:05:55.525
Could the boys get one more shot of you
coming out the door?


71
00:05:55.735 --> 00:05:58.278
Honestly, isn't all this stuff an awful bore?

72
00:05:58.488 --> 00:06:00.447
- Good to see you, Tony.
- It's nice to see you.


73
00:06:00.656 --> 00:06:04.409
By the door, please, Miss Gardner.
Once more! Here we go! Thank you.


74
00:06:04.619 --> 00:06:08.538
Miss Gardner, my paper would like
to do a Sunday feature on you.


75
