those signs just for me?

92
00:07:54.979 --> 00:07:57.022
That's cute. Piggy.

93
00:07:58.232 --> 00:07:59.858
Let's get rid of this stuff.

94
00:08:00.568 --> 00:08:02.777
This is the biggest surprise I've had.

95
00:08:07.116 --> 00:08:10.785
- Mister, can I have your autograph?
- You certainly can, gal, come here!


96
00:08:10.995 --> 00:08:12.287
That's my wife. Let go.

97
00:08:12.496 --> 00:08:14.748
Don't worry.
I'll get around to you in a minute.


98
00:08:14.957 --> 00:08:16.791
- Who's he?
- Never saw him before in my life.


99
00:08:17.001 --> 00:08:19.753
- Hello, piggy!
- Hello, yourself, you two-headed creep!


100
00:08:19.962 --> 00:08:21.546
Why didn't you say
when you were coming?


101
00:08:21.756 --> 00:08:22.922
We had to ask your agent.

102
00:08:23.132 --> 00:08:25.967
- Why didn't you send us a wire?
- I wanted to sneak in quietly.


103
00:08:26.177 --> 00:08:30.138
Believe me, I didn't have any trouble.
I want to see if you've changed in a year.


104
00:08:30.348 --> 00:08:33.642
No, Les, you haven't changed a bit.
You look desperately ill, as usual.


105
00:08:33.851 --> 00:08:35.977
- What'd you have to say that for?
- Just kidding.


106
00:08:36.187 --> 00:08:37.562
I've been feeling terrible all day.

107
00:08:37.772 --> 00:08:41.941
Kind of faint, lightheaded,
a lot of pressure here, queasy inside...


108
00:08:42.151 --> 00:08:43.568
...my pulse...
- You look great.


109
00:08:43.778 --> 00:08:47.322
As for you, that New York pallor
is like a breath of fresh air.


110
00:08:47.531 --> 00:08:51.618
You're too pretty to be a successful writer
and much too pretty to be married to that.


111
00:08:51.827 --> 00:08:53.912
That's the prettiest compliment
I've had all day!


112
00:08:54.121 --> 00:08:56.790
Come on, you two-headed lovebirds,
there's work to be done!


113
00:08:56.999 --> 00:09:00.377
- Now I have here a script of a show!
- Les, you didn't bring it.


114
00:09:00.586 --> 00:09:02.837
It's great. It's the best thing
we've ever written.


115
00:09:03.047 --> 00:09:05.340
Take it, boy. Smell it!
You can tell it's good.


116
00:09:05.549 --> 00:09:08.385
There's a great part in it for you,
nice little parts for us.


117
00:09:08.594 --> 00:09:11.346
Wait. This boy must be starving.
Let's take him to Sardi's.


118
00:09:16.435 --> 00:09:18.353
Only two blocks more, then Sardi's.

119
00:09:18.562 --> 00:09:21.439
- Shall we tell him, Lil, the big surprise?
- You tell him, Les.


120
00:09:21.649 --> 00:09:23.608
Who do you think is
going to do the show?

121
00:09:23.818 --> 00:09:27.904
Only the greatest director-producer
in town, Jeffrey Cordova.


122
00:09:28.114 --> 00:09:29.948
- Who?
- Jeff Cordova.


123
00:09:30.157 --> 00:09:32.826
We're meeting him tonight, backstage,
right after the show.


124
00:09:33.035 --> 00:09:35.537
- What did you say his name was?
- Jeffrey Cordova!


125
00:09:35.746 --> 00:09:36.830
You're not serious.

126
00:09:37.039 --> 00:09:39.165
I don't think he
ever heard of this fella.

127
00:09:39.375 --> 00:09:42.252
What's the matter? Don't you
get newspapers back in California?


128
00:09:42.461 --> 00:09:44.796
This genius directed Man in a Mousetrap...

129
00:09:45.005 --> 00:09:49.384
...The Lost Nymph, and did them both
while starring in Oedipus Rex.


130
00:09:49.593 --> 00:09:52.095
He's got three hits running,
and he's starring in one of them.


131
00:09:52.304 --> 00:09:53.513
Only one?

132
00:09:53.723 --> 00:09:57.642
This fella's fabulous, phenomenal,
fantastic! He can do anything.


133
00:09:57.852 --> 00:09:59.519
- Has he ever directed a musical?
- Oh...


134
00:09:59.729 --> 00:10:01.688
What's the difference? 
He can do anything.

135
00:10:01.897 --> 00:10:04.816
