He's a new kind of theater man, Tony.


136
00:10:05.025 --> 00:10:07.277
The theater's changed.
Lots of things have changed.


137
00:10:07.486 --> 00:10:08.987
They certainly have.

138
00:10:10.322 --> 00:10:12.615
What's happened to 42nd Street?

139
00:10:13.534 --> 00:10:17.162
I just can't get over it.
I just can't understand it.


140
00:10:17.371 --> 00:10:20.790
This used to be the great theater street
of the town. The New Amsterdam.


141
00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:23.877
I had one of my biggest successes there.
Ran a year and a half.


142
00:10:24.086 --> 00:10:27.005
Noel Coward and Gertie
were here in Private Lives in the Selwyn.


143
00:10:27.214 --> 00:10:29.174
Strictly carriage trade,
nothing but the finest.


144
00:10:29.383 --> 00:10:33.428
First show I ever did was at the Eltinge,
and I don't believe that's here anymore.


145
00:10:33.637 --> 00:10:35.722
